Harrods Sales to Chinese Rise 40% in First Quarter, FT Says

-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 
2011-05-21T08:15:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-21/harrods-sales-to-chinese-rise-40-in-first-quarter-ft-says.html
Harrods Ltd. reported a 40 percent
increase in sales to Chinese customers during the first quarter
compared with a year ago, the  Financial Times reported , citing
data provided by the department store.  Harrods said Chinese shoppers spent an average of more than
3,500 pounds ($5,680) per visit to the store, with business
boosted by the installation of 75 Chinese bank-card terminals,
according to the FT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Grant Smith in London at 
